Mother of top music executive, Michael Collins Ajereh, popularly known as Don Jazzy, has died. The music producer announced the death of his mother on his verified Instagram page on Saturday morning. He revealed that his mother died early on Saturday morning after suffering from cancer. “I am beyond devastated. I have never felt pain like this in my life but I am consoled by the good life she lived.  “I have never felt pain like this in my life. She was loved by everyone that even met her. She was so strong till the last minute for us even while she battled with cancer. “I have never typed a more difficult caption in my life. Please pray for our Mum’s soul to rest in peace and for strength for my dad, my siblings, her grandchildren and our entire family to bear this loss,” he wrote. Celebrities have started responding to the sad news and sending their condolences. Teni the entertainer, Rapper Falz, actress Bisola Aiyeola and others have sent their condolences. Billionaire philanthropist and former lawmaker, Ned Nwoko, also wrote, “May her gentle soul rest in the bossom of our Lord Jesus Christ.”